Get this:
<img src="data:png;base64," alt="Captcha">



# Find the image element (assuming the image has the 'alt' attribute as provided)
image_element = driver.find_element_by_xpath("//img[@alt='Captcha']")

# Extract the base64 string from the 'src' attribute
img_base64 = image_element.get_attribute('src')

# Remove the "data:image/png;base64," prefix
img_data = img_base64.split(",")[1]

# Decode the base64 string
img_bytes = base64.b64decode(img_data)

# Save the image using Pillow
image = Image.open(BytesIO(img_bytes))
image.save('captcha_image.png')

# Close the WebDriver
driver.quit()
